<head>DON'T</head>
    <list type="altnames">
<item>SHOULD NOT</item>
<item>MUST NOT</item>
    </list>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">別</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>COMMAND that one SHOULD NOT to ACT in a DEFINED way.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The most common prohibitive particle is wù 勿, which usually precedes transitive verbs with omitted objects.</p>
<p>2. Wú 毋 is a prohibitive particle which normally requires that any transitive verb it precedes must retain its object.</p>
<p>3. Wú 無 appears often used for wú 毋, but there is a clear tendency for the word to indicate a generalised "one should not" rather than a "don't" hic et nunc.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>別</p>
<p>不要</p>
<p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／ LU JIANMING</p>
        </div>
    </div>
